# Cursor AI Rules for Abbigliamento Personalizzato

## Project Context

- **Type**: Laravel 13 + Livewire 4 + Filament 5 e-commerce platform
- **Purpose**: Custom apparel quote-based ordering (no online payments)
- **Language**: Italian (locale: 'it')
- **Status**: MVP Week 2 - Admin Panel & Polish

## Key Architecture

### Central Data Model
- `product_variations` is the central pivot table linking: Product → Color → Size → PrintPlacement → PrintSide
- `pricing_tiers` enables quantity-based pricing
- `quotes` and `quote_items` handle customer orders (no payment processing)

### Product Types
- `standard`: Manually created via Filament
- `newwave`: Synced from external NWG GraphQL API

### External Integration
- NewWave GraphQL API sync via `ProductAvailabilityService`
- Job: `SyncNewWaveProductJob` with `sync_status` enum tracking

## Essential Commands

```bash
# Development
composer run dev          # php artisan serve + queue:listen + npm run dev
npm run dev               # Vite HMR

# Testing
php artisan test          # All tests
php artisan test --compact
php artisan test --filter=testName

# Code Quality
vendor/bin/pint --format agent
vendor/bin/rector

# Build
npm run build             # Production build
```

## Filament Patterns

### Conditional Field Visibility
```php
TextInput::make('company_name')
    ->visible(fn (Get $get): bool => $get('type') === 'business'),
```

### Reactive Fields
```php
TextInput::make('title')
    ->live(onBlur: true)
    ->afterStateUpdated(fn (Set $set, ?string $state) => $set(
        'slug',
        Str::slug($state ?? ''),
    )),
```

### Grid Layout
```php
Section::make('Details')
    ->schema([
        Grid::make(2)->schema([
            TextInput::make('first_name')->columnSpan(1),
            TextInput::make('last_name')->columnSpan(1),
            TextInput::make('bio')->columnSpanFull(),
        ]),
    ]),
```

### Common Mistakes to Avoid
- Always use `->visibility('public')` for Filament resources
- Always specify `->columnSpan()` or `->columnSpanFull()` for Grid children
- Never add `->dehydrated(false)` to fields that need saving
- Use `->relationship()` for Repeater, not `->fields()`

## Testing Patterns

### Feature Tests with RefreshDatabase
```php
use function Pest\Livewire\livewire;

livewire(ListUsers::class)
    ->assertCanSeeTableRecords($users)
    ->searchTable($users->first()->name);
```

### Livewire Component Tests
```php
livewire(CreateUser::class)
    ->fillForm(['name' => 'Test', 'email' => 'test@example.com'])
    ->call('create')
    ->assertRedirect();

assertDatabaseHas(User::class, ['email' => 'test@example.com']);
```

## Database Schema

### Core Tables
- `users`, `categories`, `products`, `colors`, `sizes`
- `print_placements`, `print_sides`
- `product_variations` (central pivot)
- `pricing_tiers`, `quotes`, `quote_items`
- `images`, `media` (Spatie Media Library)

## Routes

- `/` - Home page
- `/catalogo` - Product catalog
- `/catalogo/{category}` - Category view
- `/catalogo/{category}/{slug}` - Product detail
- `/quote` - Create quote
- `/services`, `/contact`, `/cart`, `/palette`

## Authentication

- Uses Laravel Fortify v1
- Routes: `/login`, `/register`, `/forgot-password`, `/reset-password`
- Password rules in `PasswordValidationRules` trait

## Media Library

- Collection: `images` on Product and Category models
- Conversions: `thumbnail` (150x150), `medium` (600x600), `large` (1000x1000)
- Automatic cleanup via `registerMediaConversions()`

